The Osun State Governor, Adegboyega Oyetola has described Chief Abdulkareem Adebisi Akande as a compendium of wisdom, father and an exemplary elder statesman. Governor Oyetola also described Akande who is a former governor of the state as a true progressive, peacemaker whose love for a united Nigeria is unquantifiable. In a message to mark the 83rd birthday of Chief Akande, the governor said he is a relentless statesman who is still actively working for a prosperous and democratic Nigeria. The statement was made available to DAILY POST by the Chief Press Secretary to Governor Oyetola, Ismail Omipidan, While commending Chief Akande for his service to the state in and out of office, he hailed the elder statesman for his contributions to the growth and success of the ruling All Progressives Congress (APC) having served as its first interim National Chairman. “As a quintessential administrator and a fine grassroots politician, his immense contributions to nation-building and national integration is written in the sands of time. “Again, his legacy in the political space of Osun is unmatchable. History will not forget that it was Baba Akande who birthed the legacy of prudent and transparent management of men and resources in the state. He is a compendium of wisdom,” he concluded.